A couple days ago I found out my Def Jam bredren Big Kay @jus.kay105 had passed away. I spent a lot of time in the studio with bro. One year we put out 3 mixtapes in one year. I’m talking bout fully tracked out mixes bout 20 songs per tape. That’s a lot of time. Kay was very religious. I remember when I first took a leap of faith & quit my job I asked him for advice and he told me to put my faith in God. That was a very generic answer for me and I was expecting more advice. Fast forward over the years the more I understood the things we can’t see and the spiritual world I understood that that’s his way of saying to put your faith in yourself. 
R.I.P. Big K Def Jam 🙏🏾👼🏽

From 09 to 2011 I was homeless I was sleeping in a basement shelter. I remember one day telling my twin brother I’d rather be making a living off of doing music or id rather be dead. I didn’t even work my first job yet much more I didn’t know how it was gonna happen but the whole time I knew it was gonna happen. Fast forward I been All-In 10 plus now. I be in the grind so much I tend to forget how far I’ve came. Hopefully my story inspires others and I gotta tell it more often.
